TY  - JOUR
T1  - Demand Estimation with Heterogeneous Consumers and Unobserved Product Characteristics: A Hedonic Approach
AU  - Bajari, Patrick
AU  - Benkard, C. Lanier
Y1  - 2005/12/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/498586
DO  - 10.1086/498586
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 1239
EP  - 1276
VL  - 113
IS  - 6
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - We reconsider the identification and estimation of Gorman?Lancaster?style hedonic models of demand for differentiated products in the spirit of Sherwin Rosen. We generalize Rosen?s first stage to account for product characteristics that are not observed and to allow the hedonic pricing function to have a general nonseparable form. We take an alternative semiparametric approach to Rosen?s second stage in which we assume that the parametric form of utility is known, but we place no restrictions on the aggregate distribution of utility parameters. If there are only a small number of products, we show how to construct bounds on individuals? utility parameters, as well as other economic objects such as aggregate demand and consumer surplus. We apply our methods to estimating the demand for personal computers.
AB  - We reconsider the identification and estimation of Gorman?Lancaster?style hedonic models of demand for differentiated products in the spirit of Sherwin Rosen. We generalize Rosen?s first stage to account for product characteristics that are not observed and to allow the hedonic pricing function to have a general nonseparable form. We take an alternative semiparametric approach to Rosen?s second stage in which we assume that the parametric form of utility is known, but we place no restrictions on the aggregate distribution of utility parameters. If there are only a small number of products, we show how to construct bounds on individuals? utility parameters, as well as other economic objects such as aggregate demand and consumer surplus. We apply our methods to estimating the demand for personal computers.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/498586
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/498586
Y2  - 2024/03/19
